.TH "force_sig_info_umip_fault" 9 "force_sig_info_umip_fault" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
force_sig_info_umip_fault \- Force a SIGSEGV with SEGV_MAPERR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" force_sig_info_umip_fault
.BI "(void __user *addr "  ","
.BI "struct pt_regs *regs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
Address that caused the signal
.IP "regs" 12
Register set containing the instruction pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Force a SIGSEGV signal with SEGV_MAPERR as the error code. This function is
intended to be used to provide a segmentation fault when the result of the
UMIP emulation could not be copied to the user space memory.
.SH "RETURN"
none
